1
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:10,000
[Episode 6: At Least 30 cm from Me]

2
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:15,159
Who is this?

3
00:01:15,159 --> 00:01:17,522
Eager for my zero-point dishes!

4
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,762
Get out! You're not welcome here.

5
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,580
Get out now! Get out!

6
00:01:26,580 --> 00:01:28,440
I just think if I tell you the truth,

7
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:30,800
you'd think I'm kind to you
because of the recipe.

8
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:31,840
Aren't you?

9
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,040
More than that.

10
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:35,135
I really want to thank you.

11
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,094
You achieve your goal

12
00:01:39,094 --> 00:01:40,680
and show me kindness incidentally,

13
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,600
as usual.

14
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,760
Come on.

15
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:46,350
No big deal.

16
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,160
See you next time.

17
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,289
Okay.

18
00:01:50,101 --> 00:01:51,360
You're taking this opportunity

19
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:53,090
to vent your previous anger, right?

20
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:55,359
- Excuse me.
- I admit

21
00:01:55,359 --> 00:01:57,519
I was a terrible girlfriend.

22
00:01:57,519 --> 00:01:58,840
But since we're partners,

23
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,720
we should bear no grudge.

24
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,680
You can express your reasonable needs,

25
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,560
and I'll try to make up,

26
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,715
rather than this way.

27
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:10,753
<i>Why isn't she suffering</i>

28
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,070
<i>or even regretful?</i>

29
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,160
Thanks for your belated kindness.

30
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,599
I don't need it.

31
00:02:25,599 --> 00:02:26,800
It's all in the past.

32
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:29,199
Now I'm just stating the facts.

33
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:31,840
Mutual trust is the base of cooperation.

34
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:34,038
But you aren't frank.

35
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:35,840
I'm sorry.

36
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,799
It's indeed my fault.

37
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,958
You're not angry, are you?

38
00:02:57,300 --> 00:03:01,370
[It's not a coincidence, I met you on purpose.]

39
00:03:01,370 --> 00:03:03,370
[Certificate of Honor]

40
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,415
He's definitely still angry.

41
00:03:17,415 --> 00:03:19,360
Childish?

42
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,809
Unfriend me every time we quarrel.

43
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:34,798
No.

44
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,498
Why would I care about that?

45
00:03:56,138 --> 00:03:59,000
Hello. Not me, but a friend of mine.

46
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,920
Cut the foreplay. Get to the point.

47
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,800
Her ex is mad at her.

48
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,095
She doesn't know how to mollify him.

49
00:04:05,095 --> 00:04:06,280
She wants to get back together?

50
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,400
No!

51
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,919
Just colleagues now.

52
00:04:08,919 --> 00:04:10,520
It's to facilitate work.

53
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,120
Appeal to emotions.

54
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,680
Coax him

55
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:16,240
the way he treated her.

56
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,360
Dear, if it works, please give a good review.

57
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,652
Thank you.

58
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,992
I'm sorry.

59
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,506
I'm sorry.

60
00:04:46,254 --> 00:04:48,639
We're only mildly punished with self-criticism.

61
00:04:48,639 --> 00:04:50,199
I hear he'll

62
00:04:50,199 --> 00:04:51,560
be expelled.

63
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,095
I'm sorry.

64
00:04:57,419 --> 00:04:58,440
I'm sorry.

65
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,768
Never...

66
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:06,400
You're still mad at him?

67
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,377
It hurts, okay?

68
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,399
Help me choose.

69
00:05:11,399 --> 00:05:13,400
Which dress should I buy?

70
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,841
This one.

71
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,712
Okay.

72
00:05:16,712 --> 00:05:17,959
I'll buy it.

73
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:19,640
Anything interests you?

74
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,800
If we order together,
we can save on the freight charge.

75
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,080
How?

76
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:25,120
Don't you know online shopping?

77
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,960
So outdated.

78
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,094
I know.

79
00:05:28,094 --> 00:05:29,664
Which one?

80
00:05:36,138 --> 00:05:37,200
This one.

81
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,110
It's cute. I like it.

82
00:05:41,465 --> 00:05:42,759
Okay.

83
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:43,800
280 yuan.

84
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,527
Bring me the money tomorrow.

85
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,560
Next month.

86
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,480
I'm out of pocket money this month.

87
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:52,827
It's only mid-month!

88
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,912
Everyone, get ready for class.

89
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,313
<i>Don't be mad.</i>

90
00:06:35,079 --> 00:06:37,660
<i>I'll see you the night after tomorrow.</i>

91
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:11,000
<i>You said you'd see me.</i>

92
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,480
<i>It's so late.</i>

93
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,076
<i>Where are you?</i>

94
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:41,000
After making me fall,

95
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,360
he even stood me up!

96
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:09,184
At low tide, I found it on the beach.

97
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,040
For me?

98
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,360
At high tide,

99
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:17,295
put it back into the sea.

100
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,521
Just to show me?

101
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,847
I thought it'd please you.

102
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,803
Hey!

103
00:08:41,160 --> 00:08:42,587
I want to go too.

104
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,846
I'm sorry.

105
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,730
For what?

106
00:09:16,210 --> 00:09:18,610
For my impaired left ear,

107
00:09:18,610 --> 00:09:20,938
poor balance,

108
00:09:20,938 --> 00:09:22,951
and being unable to ride.

109
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:27,120
I didn't want them to know that day.

110
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:29,440
So... I didn't say anything.

111
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,918
Sorry.

112
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:34,394
Then regard me as the ocean.

113
00:09:35,042 --> 00:09:37,600
Put your secret in it.

114
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,810
None but us

115
00:09:38,810 --> 00:09:40,683
know it.

116
00:10:25,129 --> 00:10:26,938
What do you mean, I'm not credited?

117
00:10:26,938 --> 00:10:28,680
<i>Nan Feng,</i>

118
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:31,120
<i>it's unexpected.</i>

119
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,236
<i>Besides, as an old friend,</i>

120
00:10:33,236 --> 00:10:34,760
<i>you're mad when asked for a favor.</i>

121
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,429
<i>This, this, this is simply...</i>

122
00:10:36,429 --> 00:10:38,040
<i>not a buddy's act!</i>

123
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,512
At least pay me.

124
00:10:41,799 --> 00:10:43,040
<i>I know, I know.</i>

125
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,960
<i>We're preparing the contract.</i>

126
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:47,159
<i>Hey, I'll send you an audition clip.</i>

127
00:10:47,159 --> 00:10:48,799
<i>Take a look. Don't spread.</i>

128
00:10:48,799 --> 00:10:50,440
<i>I didn't want him at first.</i>

129
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,480
<i>He's auditioned four or five times.</i>

130
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,920
<i>He said he's your buddy.</i>

131
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:55,240
<i>See if you want to keep him.</i>

132
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,720
<i>Well, I'm still on set.</i>

133
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,189
<i>The signal is bad here.</i>

134
00:10:58,189 --> 00:11:00,960
<i>Hello? Hello? Hello?</i>

135
00:11:06,864 --> 00:11:08,040
I don't know him.

136
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,655
Even if I do, you needn't keep him.

137
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,246
What's up?

138
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,760
I got it from a ring toss.

139
00:11:31,916 --> 00:11:34,010
What does it have to do with our cooperation?

140
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,880
It's dark. I dare not walk alone at night.

141
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:40,144
Can you come with me to release it?

142
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:17,360
The natural protein enzymes in kiwi

143
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:19,476
can break down proteins in meat.

144
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,840
What?

145
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:24,840
If you add kiwi to stewed meat,

146
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,470
it gets tenderer.

147
00:12:27,107 --> 00:12:28,473
You're no longer mad?

148
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,957
I never was.

149
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,040
A little.

150
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:43,820
Sorry for losing my temper with you.

151
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,638
You don't have to say "Never mind".

152
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,862
Let's go.

153
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,677
<i>Never mind.</i>

154
00:13:06,475 --> 00:13:07,476
Please,

155
00:13:07,476 --> 00:13:09,302
Mr. Drizzle.
